parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the SportShift Automatic Transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or accelerate uncontrollably, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: the vehicle loses power to the wheels
the engine revs up when pressing the gas pedal
the vehicle fails to move while in gear
the transmission fails to respond when shifting gears
the gear fails to go into reverse.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to lose motive power and stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power and stalls
the gear shifter independently shifts into gear when the vehicle is turned off.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to Cam Seal Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cam seal can cause oil to leak from the engine, leading to engine failure, loss of power, and loss of control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Oil pressure indicator light comes on

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing belt can cause sudden and dangerous loss of power, leading to accidents or leave the driver stranded.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to Multiple Component Failures
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of multiple engine components, such as the cam seal and timing belt, can cause engine failure, loss of power, and loss of control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Unexplained engine failure can cause loss of power, loss of control, and accidents.
The failure of the tire sidewall can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: Tire develops a bubble on the sidewall
tire breaks away from the sidewall
tire shows cracks on the sidewall
tire separation on the inner side wall
tire cracking on the outer wall
